4_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_096cabd402a0834ae5dafea16e8a3c7d.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/1f/1083498654_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_7589d7ecbdfafd2a28c72dde8bac657d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/1f/1083498654_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_b7f8b689c83ca38ba7d7751cbfc4390f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Evgeny Odinokov</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：几位接近展会的消息人士和公司告诉人造卫星网，原定于 7 月底举行的 2023 年国际航空航天沙龙 (MAKS-2023) 可能会推迟或取消。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “周四将开会讨论举办MAKS航展的问题。根据其结果，必须决定要么按计划在今年7月底举办展览，要么推迟到2024年举行，”一位熟悉此事的消息人士说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">其他消息人士称，MAKS-2023 可能会被取消。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> MAKS-2023 的组织者没有对取消的可能性发表评论。 Sputnik 未收到俄罗斯工业和贸易部或俄罗斯国有国防公司 Rostec 的评论。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> MAKS 每两年在俄罗斯首都东南约 40 公里（25 英里）的莫斯科地区茹科夫斯基市举行。 MAKS-2023 计划于 2023 年 7 月 25 日至 30 日举行。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 25 May 2023 04:04:48 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/maks-2023-scheduled-for-june-could-be-postponed-to-later-date-or-canceled---sources-1110575845.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/maks-2023-scheduled-for-june-could-be-postponed-to-later-date-or-canceled---sources-1110575845.html<category>军队</category><category>MAKS航展</category><category>推迟</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[GOP Voters Have Chosen Trump, DeSantis as Two Republican Favorites for 2024 - Poll]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110575523" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/11/1092329809_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_837a04c695a61af5e77ff07c986fee3f.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1092329805" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/gop-voters-have-chosen-trump-desantis-as-two-republican-favorites-for-2024---poll-1110575523.html?share-img=1092329805"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Evan Vucci</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">总统唐纳德·特朗普于 2020 年 10 月 16 日星期五抵达佛罗里达州迈尔斯堡的佛罗里达州西南国际机场时与佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯交谈。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="President Donald Trump speaks with Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis as he arrives at Southwest Florida International Airport, Friday, Oct. 16, 2020, in Fort Myers, Fla. - Sputnik International, 1920, 25.05.2023" title="唐纳德·特朗普总统于 2020 年 10 月 16 日星期五抵达佛罗里达州迈尔斯堡的佛罗里达州西南国际机场时与佛罗里达州州长罗恩·德桑蒂斯进行了交谈。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/11/1092329809_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_95ec80549841ac6c9b741db8388a808b.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/11/1092329809_0:0:3072:1728_640x0_80_0_0_49d3b6fe214f7e65dfc353232506610e.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/11/1092329809_0:0:3072:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_4909459a5a2c256ee0c113d2e59a4320.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/11/1092329809_0:0:3072:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_95ec80549841ac6c9b741db8388a808b.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Evan Vucci </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="ar1x1" data-source-sid="" alt=" - Sputnik International" title="" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/01/0b/1092187887_0:0:2048:2049_100x100_80_0_0_0c2cc4c84f89aff034cc55bb01fb6697.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">玛丽·曼利</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_manley_mary/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">该民意调查调查了 1,227 名成年人，其中包括 476 名注册共和党人和倾向共和党的独立人士。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周三公布的一项民意调查显示，超过十分之八的共和党选民表示，他们将在 2024 年美国总统大选中支持（或愿意这样做）美国前总统唐纳德特朗普或佛罗里达州州长罗恩德桑蒂斯。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该<u><a href="https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/23823977-cnn-poll-trump-leads-2024-gop-primary-field-but-voters-are-open-to-supporting-other-candidates" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">调查</a></u>是在德桑蒂斯与首席执行官埃隆马斯克宣布竞选 Twitter Spaces 总统之前发布的，该公告因其技术故障而受到<u><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/may/24/ron-desantis-elon-musk-twitter-campaign-launch-glitch" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">强烈反对</a></u>，并显示特朗普的民意调查得到了 53% 的共和党人和倾向共和党的选民的支持。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">现年 44 岁的德桑蒂斯在<u><a href="https://www.nga.org/governor/ron-desantis/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">哈佛</a></u>期间“在美国海军担任 JAG 军官”，目前正在接受 26% 的共和党选民的投票，前副总统迈克·彭斯和前联合国大使几乎没有跟进尼基·黑莉 (Nikki Haley)，两人在民意调查中仅获得 6% 的共和党选民支持。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">超过 85% 的受访者表示，他们会支持或考虑支持德桑蒂斯或特朗普。大约四分之三的受访者还表示，他们对目前的共和党候选人感到“非常”或“相当”满意，而只有 27% 的人表示他们“不太满意”或根本不满意。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但调查还发现，在上个月，57%的受访者对特朗普表示“不喜欢”，尽管这个数字比上个月有所下降。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">目前，角逐共和党提名的候选人包括美国前驻联合国大使、前南卡罗来纳州州长妮基·黑利、达拉斯商人瑞恩·宾克利和南卡罗来纳州参议员蒂姆·斯科特等竞争者。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 25 May 2023 04:02:47 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/gop-voters-have-chosen-trump-desantis-as-two-republican-favorites-for-2024---poll-1110575523.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/gop-voters-have-chosen-trump-desantis-as-two-republican-favorites-for-2024---poll-1110575523.html<category>美洲</category><category>美国政治</category><category>美国政治</category><category>轮询</category><category>民意调查</category><category>民意调查</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>罗恩德桑蒂斯</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Nuclear Tech Susceptible to ‘Spies’ - Watchdog]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110575645" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083320993_0:0:3477:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_819b85f4fe7e2aca7090cea0d802f6ff.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1083320991" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/us-nuclear-tech-susceptible-to-spies---watchdog-1110575645.html?share-img=1083320991"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Charles Dharapak</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">这张 2008 年 3 月 27 日的档案照片显示了华盛顿的五角大楼。五角大楼于 2021 年 7 月 6 日星期二表示，它正在取消与微软的云计算合同，该合同最终可能价值 100 亿美元，转而寻求与微软和亚马逊达成交易。 （美联社照片/查尔斯·达拉帕克，档案）</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="This March 27, 2008, file photo, shows the Pentagon in Washington. The Pentagon said Tuesday, July 6, 2021, that it is canceling a cloud-computing contract with Microsoft that could eventually have been worth $10 billion and will instead pursue a deal with both Microsoft and Amazon. (AP Photo/Charles Dharapak, File) - Sputnik International, 1920, 25.05.2023" title="这张 2008 年 3 月 27 日的档案照片显示了华盛顿的五角大楼。五角大楼于 2021 年 7 月 6 日星期二表示，它正在取消与微软的云计算合同，该合同最终可能价值 100 亿美元，转而寻求与微软和亚马逊达成交易。 （美联社照片/查尔斯·达拉帕克，档案）" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083320993_0:46:3477:2002_1920x0_80_0_0_43e029dba9d2d4053d0b0d47dafd9a08.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083320993_0:46:3477:2002_640x0_80_0_0_13fdffe92870268fd83bb2343cea2e4c.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083320993_0:46:3477:2002_1280x0_80_0_0_fe6846badc53a0f172309a7f05963c6f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/07/06/1083320993_0:46:3477:2002_1920x0_80_0_0_43e029dba9d2d4053d0b0d47dafd9a08.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Charles Dharapak </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">悦里德</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_wyatt_reed/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">就所谓的“内部威胁”发出警告之际，美国政府和西方媒体越来越多地将中国出生的科学家作为潜在间谍。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国政府监督组织的一份新报告称，负责监督华盛顿核机密的联邦机构在总统令下令制定“内部威胁”计划整整十年后仍未制定该计划。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “根据多项独立评估，能源部 (DOE) 在 2014 年制定内部威胁计划 8 年多后仍未实施其内部威胁计划所需的所有措施，”由政府问责办公室制作的<u><a href="https://www.gao.gov/products/gao-23-105576" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">文件</a></u>指出。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “具体来说，即使在独立审查员提出近 50 项调查结果和建议以帮助能源部全面实施其计划之后，美国能源部仍未为其内部威胁计划实施七项必要措施。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110575645" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230525/us-nuclear-tech-susceptible-to-spies---watchdog-1110575645.html?share-block=1110575648" data-title="“Specifically, DOE has not implemented seven required measures for its Insider Threat Program, even after independent reviewers made nearly 50 findings and recommendations to help DOE fully implement its program.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">更重要的是，“DOE 没有正式跟踪或报告其实施这些措施的行动，”报告补充说，并指出“如果不跟踪和报告其为解决独立审查人员的调查结果和建议而采取的行动，DOE 就无法确保它已完全解决确定的程序缺陷。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据美国政府监管机构的说法，这意味着能源部“没有确保员工接受过识别和报告潜在内部威胁的培训”，并且“没有明确定义承包商对该计划的责任”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>这份报告发表之际，美国政府主流媒体普遍指责华裔科学家正试图将美国的核机密偷运出境。</p><p>近年来，中国出生的科学家越来越成为联邦调查人员的目标，在某些情况下，他们会因签证申请中的轻微遗漏而指控研究人员犯有多项刑事罪。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">能源部发言人在一份声明中写道：“我们感谢政府问责办公室的审查，并已采取一系列行动进一步加强能源部有效阻止、检测和减轻整个核企业内部威胁的能力。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>但不用担心——该机构坚称，能源部拥有“一支经过严格审查的员工队伍，并维护专门旨在避免或尽量减少内部威胁的计划，同时利用长期保护措施防止滥用关键库存资产和资源”。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2011 年，在陆军告密者切尔西曼宁帮助揭露美军大规模不法行为的证据之后，奥巴马政府于 2011 年建立了“内部威胁”计划，甚至包括可能的战争罪。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 25 May 2023 03:57:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/us-nuclear-tech-susceptible-to-spies---watchdog-1110575645.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230525/us-nuclear-tech-susceptible-to-spies---watchdog-1110575645.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>看门狗</category><category>核技术</category><category>能源部 (DOE)</category><category>美国政府问责局 (GAO)</category><category>切尔西·曼宁</category><category>巴拉克奥巴马</category></item></channel></rss>